112/// @brief Aborts application due with user-defined status
113static void abort(int status, const std::string& reason) {
114 // Both status and reason params are there for debugging with tools like gdb etc
115 ELPP_UNUSED(status);
116 ELPP_UNUSED(reason);
117#if defined(ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC) && defined(_M_IX86) && defined(_DEBUG)
118 // Ignore msvc critical error dialog - break instead (on debug mode)
119 _asm int 3
120#else
121 ::abort();
122#endif // defined(ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC) && defined(_M_IX86) && defined(_DEBUG)
123}

132const char* LevelHelper::convertToString(Level level) {
133 // Do not use switch over strongly typed enums because Intel C++ compilers dont support them yet.
134 if (level == Level::Global) return "GLOBAL";
135 if (level == Level::Debug) return "DEBUG";
136 if (level == Level::Info) return "INFO";
137 if (level == Level::Warning) return "WARNING";
138 if (level == Level::Error) return "ERROR";
139 if (level == Level::Fatal) return "FATAL";
140 if (level == Level::Verbose) return "VERBOSE";
141 if (level == Level::Trace) return "TRACE";
142 return "UNKNOWN";
143}
144
145struct StringToLevelItem {
146 const char* levelString;
147 Level level;
148};
149
150static struct StringToLevelItem stringToLevelMap[] = {
151 { "global", Level::Global },
152 { "debug", Level::Debug },
153 { "info", Level::Info },
154 { "warning", Level::Warning },
155 { "error", Level::Error },
156 { "fatal", Level::Fatal },
157 { "verbose", Level::Verbose },
158 { "trace", Level::Trace }
159};
160
161Level LevelHelper::convertFromString(const char* levelStr) {
162 for (auto& item : stringToLevelMap) {
163 if (base::utils::Str::cStringCaseEq(levelStr, item.levelString)) {
164 return item.level;
165 }
166 }
167 return Level::Unknown;
168}
169
170void LevelHelper::forEachLevel(base::type::EnumType* startIndex, const std::function<bool(void)>& fn) {
171 base::type::EnumType lIndexMax = LevelHelper::kMaxValid;
172 do {
173 if (fn()) {
174 break;
175 }
176 *startIndex = static_cast<base::type::EnumType>(*startIndex << 1);
177 } while (*startIndex <= lIndexMax);
178}

182const char* ConfigurationTypeHelper::convertToString(ConfigurationType configurationType) {
183 // Do not use switch over strongly typed enums because Intel C++ compilers dont support them yet.
184 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::Enabled) return "ENABLED";
185 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::Filename) return "FILENAME";
186 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::Format) return "FORMAT";
187 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::ToFile) return "TO_FILE";
188 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::ToStandardOutput) return "TO_STANDARD_OUTPUT";
189 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::SubsecondPrecision) return "SUBSECOND_PRECISION";
190 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::PerformanceTracking) return "PERFORMANCE_TRACKING";
191 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::MaxLogFileSize) return "MAX_LOG_FILE_SIZE";
192 if (configurationType == ConfigurationType::LogFlushThreshold) return "LOG_FLUSH_THRESHOLD";
193 return "UNKNOWN";
194}

214ConfigurationType ConfigurationTypeHelper::convertFromString(const char* configStr) {
215 for (auto& item : configStringToTypeMap) {

257void Configuration::log(el::base::type::ostream_t& os) const {
258 os << LevelHelper::convertToString(m_level)
259 << ELPP_LITERAL(" ") << ConfigurationTypeHelper::convertToString(m_configurationType)
260 << ELPP_LITERAL(" = ") << m_value.c_str();
261}

280Configurations::Configurations(const std::string& configurationFile, bool useDefaultsForRemaining,
281 Configurations* base) :
282 m_configurationFile(configurationFile),
283 m_isFromFile(false) {
284 parseFromFile(configurationFile, base);
285 if (useDefaultsForRemaining) {
286 setRemainingToDefault();
287 }

289
290bool Configurations::parseFromFile(const std::string& configurationFile, Configurations* base) {
291 // We initial assertion with true because if we have assertion disabled, we want to pass this
292 // check and if assertion is enabled we will have values re-assigned any way.
293 bool assertionPassed = true;
294 ELPP_ASSERT((assertionPassed = base::utils::File::pathExists(configurationFile.c_str(), true)) == true,
295 "Configuration file [" << configurationFile << "] does not exist!");
296 if (!assertionPassed) {
297 return false;
298 }
299 bool success = Parser::parseFromFile(configurationFile, this, base);
300 m_isFromFile = success;
301 return success;
302}
303
304bool Configurations::parseFromText(const std::string& configurationsString, Configurations* base) {
305 bool success = Parser::parseFromText(configurationsString, this, base);
306 if (success) {
307 m_isFromFile = false;
308 }
309 return success;
310}
311
312void Configurations::setFromBase(Configurations* base) {
313 if (base == nullptr || base == this) {
314 return;
315 }
316 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(base->lock());
317 for (Configuration*& conf : base->list()) {
318 set(conf);
319 }
320}
321
322bool Configurations::hasConfiguration(ConfigurationType configurationType) {
323 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
324 bool result = false;
325 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
326 if (hasConfiguration(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex), configurationType)) {
327 result = true;
328 }
329 return result;
330 });
331 return result;
332}
333
334bool Configurations::hasConfiguration(Level level, ConfigurationType configurationType) {
335 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
336#if ELPP_COMPILER_INTEL
337 // We cant specify template types here, Intel C++ throws compilation error
338 // "error: type name is not allowed"
339 return RegistryWithPred::get(level, configurationType) != nullptr;
340#else
341 return RegistryWithPred<Configuration, Configuration::Predicate>::get(level, configurationType) != nullptr;
342#endif // ELPP_COMPILER_INTEL
343}
344
345void Configurations::set(Level level, ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value) {
346 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
347 unsafeSet(level, configurationType, value); // This is not unsafe anymore as we have locked mutex
348 if (level == Level::Global) {
349 unsafeSetGlobally(configurationType, value, false); // Again this is not unsafe either
350 }
351}
352
353void Configurations::set(Configuration* conf) {
354 if (conf == nullptr) {
355 return;
356 }
357 set(conf->level(), conf->configurationType(), conf->value());
358}

360void Configurations::setToDefault(void) {
361 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::Enabled, std::string("true"), true);
362 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::Filename, std::string(base::consts::kDefaultLogFile), true);
363#if defined(ELPP_NO_LOG_TO_FILE)
364 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::ToFile, std::string("false"), true);
365#else
366 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::ToFile, std::string("true"), true);
367#endif // defined(ELPP_NO_LOG_TO_FILE)
368 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::ToStandardOutput, std::string("true"), true);
369 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::SubsecondPrecision, std::string("3"), true);
370 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::PerformanceTracking, std::string("true"), true);
371 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::MaxLogFileSize, std::string("0"), true);
372 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::LogFlushThreshold, std::string("0"), true);
373
374 setGlobally(ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"), true);
375 set(Level::Debug, ConfigurationType::Format,
376 std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] [%user@%host] [%func] [%loc] %msg"));
377 // INFO and WARNING are set to default by Level::Global
378 set(Level::Error, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"));
379 set(Level::Fatal, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"));
380 set(Level::Verbose, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level-%vlevel [%logger] %msg"));
381 set(Level::Trace, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] [%func] [%loc] %msg"));
382}

384void Configurations::setRemainingToDefault(void) {
385 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
386#if defined(ELPP_NO_LOG_TO_FILE)
387 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::Enabled, std::string("false"));
388#else
389 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::Enabled, std::string("true"));
390#endif // defined(ELPP_NO_LOG_TO_FILE)
391 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::Filename, std::string(base::consts::kDefaultLogFile));
392 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::ToStandardOutput, std::string("true"));
393 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::SubsecondPrecision, std::string("3"));
394 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::PerformanceTracking, std::string("true"));
395 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::MaxLogFileSize, std::string("0"));
396 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"));
397 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Debug, ConfigurationType::Format,
398 std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] [%user@%host] [%func] [%loc] %msg"));
399 // INFO and WARNING are set to default by Level::Global
400 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Error, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"));
401 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Fatal, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] %msg"));
402 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Verbose, ConfigurationType::Format, std::string("%datetime %level-%vlevel [%logger] %msg"));
403 unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level::Trace, ConfigurationType::Format,
404 std::string("%datetime %level [%logger] [%func] [%loc] %msg"));
405}

407bool Configurations::Parser::parseFromFile(const std::string& configurationFile, Configurations* sender,
408 Configurations* base) {
409 sender->setFromBase(base);
410 std::ifstream fileStream_(configurationFile.c_str(), std::ifstream::in);
411 ELPP_ASSERT(fileStream_.is_open(), "Unable to open configuration file [" << configurationFile << "] for parsing.");
412 bool parsedSuccessfully = false;
413 std::string line = std::string();
414 Level currLevel = Level::Unknown;
415 std::string currConfigStr = std::string();
416 std::string currLevelStr = std::string();
417 while (fileStream_.good()) {
418 std::getline(fileStream_, line);
419 parsedSuccessfully = parseLine(&line, &currConfigStr, &currLevelStr, &currLevel, sender);
420 ELPP_ASSERT(parsedSuccessfully, "Unable to parse configuration line: " << line);
421 }
422 return parsedSuccessfully;
423}
424
425bool Configurations::Parser::parseFromText(const std::string& configurationsString, Configurations* sender,
426 Configurations* base) {
427 sender->setFromBase(base);
428 bool parsedSuccessfully = false;
429 std::stringstream ss(configurationsString);
430 std::string line = std::string();
431 Level currLevel = Level::Unknown;
432 std::string currConfigStr = std::string();
433 std::string currLevelStr = std::string();
434 while (std::getline(ss, line)) {
435 parsedSuccessfully = parseLine(&line, &currConfigStr, &currLevelStr, &currLevel, sender);
436 ELPP_ASSERT(parsedSuccessfully, "Unable to parse configuration line: " << line);
437 }
438 return parsedSuccessfully;
439}

441void Configurations::Parser::ignoreComments(std::string* line) {
442 std::size_t foundAt = 0;
443 std::size_t quotesStart = line->find("\"");
444 std::size_t quotesEnd = std::string::npos;
445 if (quotesStart != std::string::npos) {
446 quotesEnd = line->find("\"", quotesStart + 1);
447 while (quotesEnd != std::string::npos && line->at(quotesEnd - 1) == '\\') {
448 // Do not erase slash yet - we will erase it in parseLine(..) while loop
449 quotesEnd = line->find("\"", quotesEnd + 2);
450 }
451 }
452 if ((foundAt = line->find(base::consts::kConfigurationComment)) != std::string::npos) {
453 if (foundAt < quotesEnd) {
454 foundAt = line->find(base::consts::kConfigurationComment, quotesEnd + 1);
455 }
456 *line = line->substr(0, foundAt);
457 }
458}

460bool Configurations::Parser::isLevel(const std::string& line) {
461 return base::utils::Str::startsWith(line, std::string(base::consts::kConfigurationLevel));
462}
463
464bool Configurations::Parser::isComment(const std::string& line) {
465 return base::utils::Str::startsWith(line, std::string(base::consts::kConfigurationComment));
466}
467
468bool Configurations::Parser::isConfig(const std::string& line) {
469 std::size_t assignment = line.find('=');
470 return line != "" &&
471 ((line[0] >= 'A' && line[0] <= 'Z') || (line[0] >= 'a' && line[0] <= 'z')) &&
472 (assignment != std::string::npos) &&
473 (line.size() > assignment);
474}
475
476bool Configurations::Parser::parseLine(std::string* line, std::string* currConfigStr, std::string* currLevelStr,
477 Level* currLevel,
478 Configurations* conf) {
479 ConfigurationType currConfig = ConfigurationType::Unknown;
480 std::string currValue = std::string();
481 *line = base::utils::Str::trim(*line);
482 if (isComment(*line)) return true;
483 ignoreComments(line);
484 *line = base::utils::Str::trim(*line);
485 if (line->empty()) {
486 // Comment ignored
487 return true;
488 }
489 if (isLevel(*line)) {
490 if (line->size() <= 2) {
491 return true;
492 }
493 *currLevelStr = line->substr(1, line->size() - 2);
494 *currLevelStr = base::utils::Str::toUpper(*currLevelStr);
495 *currLevelStr = base::utils::Str::trim(*currLevelStr);
496 *currLevel = LevelHelper::convertFromString(currLevelStr->c_str());
497 return true;
498 }
499 if (isConfig(*line)) {
500 std::size_t assignment = line->find('=');
501 *currConfigStr = line->substr(0, assignment);
502 *currConfigStr = base::utils::Str::toUpper(*currConfigStr);
503 *currConfigStr = base::utils::Str::trim(*currConfigStr);
504 currConfig = ConfigurationTypeHelper::convertFromString(currConfigStr->c_str());
505 currValue = line->substr(assignment + 1);
506 currValue = base::utils::Str::trim(currValue);
507 std::size_t quotesStart = currValue.find("\"", 0);
508 std::size_t quotesEnd = std::string::npos;
509 if (quotesStart != std::string::npos) {
510 quotesEnd = currValue.find("\"", quotesStart + 1);
511 while (quotesEnd != std::string::npos && currValue.at(quotesEnd - 1) == '\\') {
512 currValue = currValue.erase(quotesEnd - 1, 1);
513 quotesEnd = currValue.find("\"", quotesEnd + 2);
514 }
515 }
516 if (quotesStart != std::string::npos && quotesEnd != std::string::npos) {
517 // Quote provided - check and strip if valid
518 ELPP_ASSERT((quotesStart < quotesEnd), "Configuration error - No ending quote found in ["
519 << currConfigStr << "]");
520 ELPP_ASSERT((quotesStart + 1 != quotesEnd), "Empty configuration value for [" << currConfigStr << "]");
521 if ((quotesStart != quotesEnd) && (quotesStart + 1 != quotesEnd)) {
522 // Explicit check in case if assertion is disabled
523 currValue = currValue.substr(quotesStart + 1, quotesEnd - 1);
524 }
525 }
526 }
527 ELPP_ASSERT(*currLevel != Level::Unknown, "Unrecognized severity level [" << *currLevelStr << "]");
528 ELPP_ASSERT(currConfig != ConfigurationType::Unknown, "Unrecognized configuration [" << *currConfigStr << "]");
529 if (*currLevel == Level::Unknown || currConfig == ConfigurationType::Unknown) {
530 return false; // unrecognizable level or config
531 }
532 conf->set(*currLevel, currConfig, currValue);
533 return true;
534}

536void Configurations::unsafeSetIfNotExist(Level level, ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value) {
537 Configuration* conf = RegistryWithPred<Configuration, Configuration::Predicate>::get(level, configurationType);
538 if (conf == nullptr) {
539 unsafeSet(level, configurationType, value);
540 }
541}
542
543void Configurations::unsafeSet(Level level, ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value) {
544 Configuration* conf = RegistryWithPred<Configuration, Configuration::Predicate>::get(level, configurationType);
545 if (conf == nullptr) {
546 registerNew(new Configuration(level, configurationType, value));
547 } else {
548 conf->setValue(value);
549 }
550 if (level == Level::Global) {
551 unsafeSetGlobally(configurationType, value, false);
552 }
553}
554
555void Configurations::setGlobally(ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value,
556 bool includeGlobalLevel) {
557 if (includeGlobalLevel) {
558 set(Level::Global, configurationType, value);
559 }
560 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
561 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
562 set(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex), configurationType, value);
563 return false; // Do not break lambda function yet as we need to set all levels regardless
564 });
565}
566
567void Configurations::unsafeSetGlobally(ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value,
568 bool includeGlobalLevel) {
569 if (includeGlobalLevel) {
570 unsafeSet(Level::Global, configurationType, value);
571 }
572 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
573 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
574 unsafeSet(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex), configurationType, value);
575 return false; // Do not break lambda function yet as we need to set all levels regardless
576 });
577}

579// LogBuilder
580
581void LogBuilder::convertToColoredOutput(base::type::string_t* logLine, Level level) {
582 if (!m_termSupportsColor) return;
583 const base::type::char_t* resetColor = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[0m");
584 if (level == Level::Error || level == Level::Fatal)
585 *logLine = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[31m") + *logLine + resetColor;
586 else if (level == Level::Warning)
587 *logLine = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[33m") + *logLine + resetColor;
588 else if (level == Level::Debug)
589 *logLine = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[32m") + *logLine + resetColor;
590 else if (level == Level::Info)
591 *logLine = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[36m") + *logLine + resetColor;
592 else if (level == Level::Trace)
593 *logLine = ELPP_LITERAL("\x1b[35m") + *logLine + resetColor;
594}

642
643void Logger::configure(const Configurations& configurations) {
644 m_isConfigured = false; // we set it to false in case if we fail
645 initUnflushedCount();
646 if (m_typedConfigurations != nullptr) {
647 Configurations* c = const_cast<Configurations*>(m_typedConfigurations->configurations());
648 if (c->hasConfiguration(Level::Global, ConfigurationType::Filename)) {
649 flush();
650 }
651 }
652 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
653 if (m_configurations != configurations) {
654 m_configurations.setFromBase(const_cast<Configurations*>(&configurations));
655 }
656 base::utils::safeDelete(m_typedConfigurations);
657 m_typedConfigurations = new base::TypedConfigurations(&m_configurations, m_logStreamsReference);
658 resolveLoggerFormatSpec();
659 m_isConfigured = true;
660}
661
662void Logger::reconfigure(void) {
663 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Reconfiguring logger [" << m_id << "]");
664 configure(m_configurations);
665}
666
667bool Logger::isValidId(const std::string& id) {
668 for (std::string::const_iterator it = id.begin(); it != id.end(); ++it) {
669 if (!base::utils::Str::contains(base::consts::kValidLoggerIdSymbols, *it)) {
670 return false;
671 }
672 }
673 return true;
674}
675
676void Logger::flush(void) {
677 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(3, "Flushing logger [" << m_id << "] all levels");
678 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
679 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
680 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
681 flush(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex), nullptr);
682 return false;
683 });
684}
685
686void Logger::flush(Level level, base::type::fstream_t* fs) {
687 if (fs == nullptr && m_typedConfigurations->toFile(level)) {
688 fs = m_typedConfigurations->fileStream(level);
689 }
690 if (fs != nullptr) {
691 fs->flush();
692 std::unordered_map<Level, unsigned int>::iterator iter = m_unflushedCount.find(level);
693 if (iter != m_unflushedCount.end()) {
694 iter->second = 0;
695 }
696 Helpers::validateFileRolling(this, level);
697 }
698}
699
700void Logger::initUnflushedCount(void) {
701 m_unflushedCount.clear();
702 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
703 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
704 m_unflushedCount.insert(std::make_pair(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex), 0));
705 return false;
706 });
707}
708
709void Logger::resolveLoggerFormatSpec(void) const {
710 base::type::EnumType lIndex = LevelHelper::kMinValid;
711 LevelHelper::forEachLevel(&lIndex, [&](void) -> bool {
712 base::LogFormat* logFormat =
713 const_cast<base::LogFormat*>(&m_typedConfigurations->logFormat(LevelHelper::castFromInt(lIndex)));
714 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logFormat->m_format, base::consts::kLoggerIdFormatSpecifier, m_id);
715 return false;
716 });
717}

727base::type::fstream_t* File::newFileStream(const std::string& filename) {
728 base::type::fstream_t *fs = new base::type::fstream_t(filename.c_str(),
729 base::type::fstream_t::out
730#if !defined(ELPP_FRESH_LOG_FILE)
731 | base::type::fstream_t::app
732#endif
733 );
734#if defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
735 std::locale elppUnicodeLocale("");
736# if ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
737 std::locale elppUnicodeLocaleWindows(elppUnicodeLocale, new std::codecvt_utf8_utf16<wchar_t>);
738 elppUnicodeLocale = elppUnicodeLocaleWindows;
739# endif // ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
740 fs->imbue(elppUnicodeLocale);
741#endif // defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
742 if (fs->is_open()) {
743 fs->flush();
744 } else {
745 base::utils::safeDelete(fs);
746 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Bad file [" << filename << "]", true);
747 }
748 return fs;
749}

752 if (fs == nullptr) {
753 return 0;

756 // offset is the file size.
757 std::size_t size = static_cast<std::size_t>(fs->tellg());
758 return size;
759}
760
761bool File::pathExists(const char* path, bool considerFile) {
762 if (path == nullptr) {
763 return false;
764 }
765#if ELPP_OS_UNIX
766 ELPP_UNUSED(considerFile);
767 struct stat st;
768 return (stat(path, &st) == 0);
769#elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
770 DWORD fileType = GetFileAttributesA(path);
771 if (fileType == INVALID_FILE_ATTRIBUTES) {
772 return false;
773 }
774 return considerFile ? true : ((fileType & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY) == 0 ? false : true);
775#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
776}
777
778bool File::createPath(const std::string& path) {
779 if (path.empty()) {
780 return false;
781 }
782 if (base::utils::File::pathExists(path.c_str())) {
783 return true;
784 }
785 int status = -1;
786
787 char* currPath = const_cast<char*>(path.c_str());
788 std::string builtPath = std::string();
789#if ELPP_OS_UNIX
790 if (path[0] == '/') {
791 builtPath = "/";
792 }
793 currPath = STRTOK(currPath, base::consts::kFilePathSeparator, 0);
794#elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
795 // Use secure functions API
796 char* nextTok_ = nullptr;
797 currPath = STRTOK(currPath, base::consts::kFilePathSeparator, &nextTok_);
798 ELPP_UNUSED(nextTok_);
799#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
800 while (currPath != nullptr) {
801 builtPath.append(currPath);
802 builtPath.append(base::consts::kFilePathSeparator);
803#if ELPP_OS_UNIX
804 status = mkdir(builtPath.c_str(), ELPP_LOG_PERMS);
805 currPath = STRTOK(nullptr, base::consts::kFilePathSeparator, 0);
806#elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
807 status = _mkdir(builtPath.c_str());
808 currPath = STRTOK(nullptr, base::consts::kFilePathSeparator, &nextTok_);
809#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
810 }
811 if (status == -1) {
812 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Error while creating path [" << path << "]", true);
813 return false;
814 }
815 return true;
816}
817
818std::string File::extractPathFromFilename(const std::string& fullPath, const char* separator) {
819 if ((fullPath == "") || (fullPath.find(separator) == std::string::npos)) {
820 return fullPath;
821 }
822 std::size_t lastSlashAt = fullPath.find_last_of(separator);
823 if (lastSlashAt == 0) {
824 return std::string(separator);
825 }
826 return fullPath.substr(0, lastSlashAt + 1);
827}

829void File::buildStrippedFilename(const char* filename, char buff[], std::size_t limit) {
830 std::size_t sizeOfFilename = strlen(filename);
831 if (sizeOfFilename >= limit) {
832 filename += (sizeOfFilename - limit);
833 if (filename[0] != '.' && filename[1] != '.') { // prepend if not already
834 filename += 3; // 3 = '..'
835 STRCAT(buff, "..", limit);
836 }
837 }
838 STRCAT(buff, filename, limit);
839}
840
841void File::buildBaseFilename(const std::string& fullPath, char buff[], std::size_t limit, const char* separator) {
842 const char *filename = fullPath.c_str();
843 std::size_t lastSlashAt = fullPath.find_last_of(separator);
844 filename += lastSlashAt ? lastSlashAt+1 : 0;
845 std::size_t sizeOfFilename = strlen(filename);
846 if (sizeOfFilename >= limit) {
847 filename += (sizeOfFilename - limit);
848 if (filename[0] != '.' && filename[1] != '.') { // prepend if not already
849 filename += 3; // 3 = '..'
850 STRCAT(buff, "..", limit);
851 }
852 }
853 STRCAT(buff, filename, limit);
854}

858bool Str::wildCardMatch(const char* str, const char* pattern) {
859 while (*pattern) {
860 switch (*pattern) {
861 case '?':
862 if (!*str)
863 return false;
864 ++str;
865 ++pattern;
866 break;
867 case '*':
868 if (wildCardMatch(str, pattern + 1))
869 return true;
870 if (*str && wildCardMatch(str + 1, pattern))
871 return true;
872 return false;
873 default:
874 if (*str++ != *pattern++)
875 return false;
876 break;
877 }
878 }
879 return !*str && !*pattern;
880}

884 return !std::isspace(c);

886 return str;
887}

894}

913std::string& Str::replaceAll(std::string& str, const std::string& replaceWhat,
914 const std::string& replaceWith) {
915 if (replaceWhat == replaceWith)
916 return str;
917 std::size_t foundAt = std::string::npos;
918 while ((foundAt = str.find(replaceWhat, foundAt + 1)) != std::string::npos) {
919 str.replace(foundAt, replaceWhat.length(), replaceWith);
920 }
921 return str;
922}
923
924void Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(base::type::string_t& str, const base::type::string_t& replaceWhat,
925 const base::type::string_t& replaceWith) {
926 std::size_t foundAt = base::type::string_t::npos;
927 while ((foundAt = str.find(replaceWhat, foundAt + 1)) != base::type::string_t::npos) {
928 if (foundAt > 0 && str[foundAt - 1] == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar) {
929 str.erase(foundAt - 1, 1);
930 ++foundAt;
931 } else {
932 str.replace(foundAt, replaceWhat.length(), replaceWith);
933 return;
934 }
935 }
936}

941}

957
958bool Str::cStringCaseEq(const char* s1, const char* s2) {
959 if (s1 == nullptr && s2 == nullptr) return true;
960 if (s1 == nullptr || s2 == nullptr) return false;
961
962 // With thanks to cygwin for this code
963 int d = 0;
964
965 while (true) {
966 const int c1 = toupper(*s1++);
967 const int c2 = toupper(*s2++);
968
969 if (((d = c1 - c2) != 0) || (c2 == '\0')) {
970 break;
971 }
972 }
973
974 return d == 0;
975}

985char* Str::convertAndAddToBuff(std::size_t n, int len, char* buf, const char* bufLim, bool zeroPadded) {
986 char localBuff[10] = "";
987 char* p = localBuff + sizeof(localBuff) - 2;
988 if (n > 0) {
989 for (; n > 0 && p > localBuff && len > 0; n /= 10, --len)
990 *--p = static_cast<char>(n % 10 + '0');
991 } else {
992 *--p = '0';
993 --len;
994 }
995 if (zeroPadded)
996 while (p > localBuff && len-- > 0) *--p = static_cast<char>('0');
997 return addToBuff(p, buf, bufLim);
998}
999
1000char* Str::addToBuff(const char* str, char* buf, const char* bufLim) {
1001 while ((buf < bufLim) && ((*buf = *str++) != '\0'))
1002 ++buf;
1003 return buf;
1004}

1012/// @brief Converts wchar* to char*
1013/// NOTE: Need to free return value after use!
1014char* Str::wcharPtrToCharPtr(const wchar_t* line) {
1015 std::size_t len_ = wcslen(line) + 1;
1016 char* buff_ = static_cast<char*>(malloc(len_ + 1));
1017# if ELPP_OS_UNIX || (ELPP_OS_WINDOWS && !ELPP_CRT_DBG_WARNINGS)
1018 std::wcstombs(buff_, line, len_);
1019# elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1020 std::size_t convCount_ = 0;
1021 mbstate_t mbState_;
1022 ::memset(static_cast<void*>(&mbState_), 0, sizeof(mbState_));
1023 wcsrtombs_s(&convCount_, buff_, len_, &line, len_, &mbState_);
1024# endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX || (ELPP_OS_WINDOWS && !ELPP_CRT_DBG_WARNINGS)
1025 return buff_;
1026}

1063const std::string OS::getBashOutput(const char* command) {
1064#if (ELPP_OS_UNIX && !ELPP_OS_ANDROID && !ELPP_CYGWIN)
1065 if (command == nullptr) {
1066 return std::string();
1067 }
1068 FILE* proc = nullptr;
1069 if ((proc = popen(command, "r")) == nullptr) {
1070 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("\nUnable to run command [" << command << "]", true);
1071 return std::string();
1072 }
1073 char hBuff[4096];
1074 if (fgets(hBuff, sizeof(hBuff), proc) != nullptr) {
1075 pclose(proc);
1076 const std::size_t buffLen = strlen(hBuff);
1077 if (buffLen > 0 && hBuff[buffLen - 1] == '\n') {
1078 hBuff[buffLen - 1] = '\0';
1079 }
1080 return std::string(hBuff);
1081 } else {
1082 pclose(proc);
1083 }
1084 return std::string();
1085#else
1086 ELPP_UNUSED(command);
1087 return std::string();
1088#endif // (ELPP_OS_UNIX && !ELPP_OS_ANDROID && !ELPP_CYGWIN)
1089}

1095#elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1096 const char* val = getWindowsEnvironmentVariable(variableName);
1097#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
1098 if ((val == nullptr) || ((strcmp(val, "") == 0))) {
1099#if ELPP_OS_UNIX && defined(ELPP_FORCE_ENV_VAR_FROM_BASH)
1100 // Try harder on unix-based systems
1101 std::string valBash = base::utils::OS::getBashOutput(alternativeBashCommand);
1102 if (valBash.empty()) {
1103 return std::string(defaultVal);
1104 } else {
1105 return valBash;
1106 }
1107#elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS || ELPP_OS_UNIX
1108 ELPP_UNUSED(alternativeBashCommand);
1109 return std::string(defaultVal);
1110#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX && defined(ELPP_FORCE_ENV_VAR_FROM_BASH)
1111 }
1112 return std::string(val);
1113}

1148// DateTime
1149
1150void DateTime::gettimeofday(struct timeval* tv) {
1151#if ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1152 if (tv != nullptr) {
1153# if ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC || defined(_MSC_EXTENSIONS)
1154 const unsigned __int64 delta_ = 11644473600000000Ui64;
1155# else
1156 const unsigned __int64 delta_ = 11644473600000000ULL;
1157# endif // ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC || defined(_MSC_EXTENSIONS)
1158 const double secOffSet = 0.000001;
1159 const unsigned long usecOffSet = 1000000;
1160 FILETIME fileTime;
1161 GetSystemTimeAsFileTime(&fileTime);
1162 unsigned __int64 present = 0;
1163 present |= fileTime.dwHighDateTime;
1164 present = present << 32;
1165 present |= fileTime.dwLowDateTime;
1166 present /= 10; // mic-sec
1167 // Subtract the difference
1168 present -= delta_;
1169 tv->tv_sec = static_cast<long>(present * secOffSet);
1170 tv->tv_usec = static_cast<long>(present % usecOffSet);
1171 }
1172#else
1173 ::gettimeofday(tv, nullptr);
1174#endif // ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1175}

1177std::string DateTime::getDateTime(const char* format, const base::SubsecondPrecision* ssPrec) {
1178 struct timeval currTime;
1179 gettimeofday(&currTime);
1180 return timevalToString(currTime, format, ssPrec);
1181}

1183std::string DateTime::timevalToString(struct timeval tval, const char* format,
1184 const el::base::SubsecondPrecision* ssPrec) {
1185 struct ::tm timeInfo;
1186 buildTimeInfo(&tval, &timeInfo);
1187 const int kBuffSize = 30;
1188 char buff_[kBuffSize] = "";
1189 parseFormat(buff_, kBuffSize, format, &timeInfo, static_cast<std::size_t>(tval.tv_usec / ssPrec->m_offset),
1190 ssPrec);
1191 return std::string(buff_);
1192}
1193
1194base::type::string_t DateTime::formatTime(unsigned long long time, base::TimestampUnit timestampUnit) {
1195 base::type::EnumType start = static_cast<base::type::EnumType>(timestampUnit);
1196 const base::type::char_t* unit = base::consts::kTimeFormats[start].unit;
1197 for (base::type::EnumType i = start; i < base::consts::kTimeFormatsCount - 1; ++i) {
1198 if (time <= base::consts::kTimeFormats[i].value) {
1199 break;
1200 }
1201 if (base::consts::kTimeFormats[i].value == 1000.0f && time / 1000.0f < 1.9f) {
1202 break;
1203 }
1204 time /= static_cast<decltype(time)>(base::consts::kTimeFormats[i].value);
1205 unit = base::consts::kTimeFormats[i + 1].unit;
1206 }
1207 base::type::stringstream_t ss;
1208 ss << time << " " << unit;
1209 return ss.str();
1210}
1211
1212unsigned long long DateTime::getTimeDifference(const struct timeval& endTime, const struct timeval& startTime,
1213 base::TimestampUnit timestampUnit) {
1214 if (timestampUnit == base::TimestampUnit::Microsecond) {
1215 return static_cast<unsigned long long>(static_cast<unsigned long long>(1000000 * endTime.tv_sec + endTime.tv_usec) -
1216 static_cast<unsigned long long>(1000000 * startTime.tv_sec + startTime.tv_usec));
1217 }
1218 // milliseconds
1219 auto conv = [](const struct timeval& tim) {
1220 return static_cast<unsigned long long>((tim.tv_sec * 1000) + (tim.tv_usec / 1000));
1221 };
1222 return static_cast<unsigned long long>(conv(endTime) - conv(startTime));
1223}
1224
1225struct ::tm* DateTime::buildTimeInfo(struct timeval* currTime, struct ::tm* timeInfo) {
1226#if ELPP_OS_UNIX
1227 time_t rawTime = currTime->tv_sec;
1228 ::elpptime_r(&rawTime, timeInfo);
1229 return timeInfo;
1230#else
1231# if ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC
1232 ELPP_UNUSED(currTime);
1233 time_t t;
1234# if defined(_USE_32BIT_TIME_T)
1235 _time32(&t);
1236# else
1237 _time64(&t);
1238# endif
1239 elpptime_s(timeInfo, &t);
1240 return timeInfo;
1241# else
1242 // For any other compilers that don't have CRT warnings issue e.g, MinGW or TDM GCC- we use different method
1243 time_t rawTime = currTime->tv_sec;
1244 struct tm* tmInf = elpptime(&rawTime);
1245 *timeInfo = *tmInf;
1246 return timeInfo;
1247# endif // ELPP_COMPILER_MSVC
1248#endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
1249}
1250
1251char* DateTime::parseFormat(char* buf, std::size_t bufSz, const char* format, const struct tm* tInfo,
1252 std::size_t msec, const base::SubsecondPrecision* ssPrec) {
1253 const char* bufLim = buf + bufSz;
1254 for (; *format; ++format) {
1255 if (*format == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar) {
1256 switch (*++format) {
1257 case base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar: // Escape
1258 break;
1259 case '\0': // End
1260 --format;
1261 break;
1262 case 'd': // Day
1263 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_mday, 2, buf, bufLim);
1264 continue;
1265 case 'a': // Day of week (short)
1266 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(base::consts::kDaysAbbrev[tInfo->tm_wday], buf, bufLim);
1267 continue;
1268 case 'A': // Day of week (long)
1269 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(base::consts::kDays[tInfo->tm_wday], buf, bufLim);
1270 continue;
1271 case 'M': // month
1272 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_mon + 1, 2, buf, bufLim);
1273 continue;
1274 case 'b': // month (short)
1275 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(base::consts::kMonthsAbbrev[tInfo->tm_mon], buf, bufLim);
1276 continue;
1277 case 'B': // month (long)
1278 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(base::consts::kMonths[tInfo->tm_mon], buf, bufLim);
1279 continue;
1280 case 'y': // year (two digits)
1281 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_year + base::consts::kYearBase, 2, buf, bufLim);
1282 continue;
1283 case 'Y': // year (four digits)
1284 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_year + base::consts::kYearBase, 4, buf, bufLim);
1285 continue;
1286 case 'h': // hour (12-hour)
1287 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_hour % 12, 2, buf, bufLim);
1288 continue;
1289 case 'H': // hour (24-hour)
1290 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_hour, 2, buf, bufLim);
1291 continue;
1292 case 'm': // minute
1293 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_min, 2, buf, bufLim);
1294 continue;
1295 case 's': // second
1296 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(tInfo->tm_sec, 2, buf, bufLim);
1297 continue;
1298 case 'z': // subsecond part
1299 case 'g':
1300 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(msec, ssPrec->m_width, buf, bufLim);
1301 continue;
1302 case 'F': // AM/PM
1303 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff((tInfo->tm_hour >= 12) ? base::consts::kPm : base::consts::kAm, buf, bufLim);
1304 continue;
1305 default:
1306 continue;
1307 }
1308 }
1309 if (buf == bufLim) break;
1310 *buf++ = *format;
1311 }
1312 return buf;
1313}
1314
1315// CommandLineArgs
1316
1317void CommandLineArgs::setArgs(int argc, char** argv) {
1318 m_params.clear();
1319 m_paramsWithValue.clear();
1320 if (argc == 0 || argv == nullptr) {
1321 return;
1322 }
1323 m_argc = argc;
1324 m_argv = argv;
1325 for (int i = 1; i < m_argc; ++i) {
1326 const char* v = (strstr(m_argv[i], "="));
1327 if (v != nullptr && strlen(v) > 0) {
1328 std::string key = std::string(m_argv[i]);
1329 key = key.substr(0, key.find_first_of('='));
1330 if (hasParamWithValue(key.c_str())) {
1331 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Skipping [" << key << "] arg since it already has value ["
1332 << getParamValue(key.c_str()) << "]");
1333 } else {
1334 m_paramsWithValue.insert(std::make_pair(key, std::string(v + 1)));
1335 }
1336 }
1337 if (v == nullptr) {
1338 if (hasParam(m_argv[i])) {
1339 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Skipping [" << m_argv[i] << "] arg since it already exists");
1340 } else {
1341 m_params.push_back(std::string(m_argv[i]));
1342 }
1343 }
1344 }
1345}
1346
1347bool CommandLineArgs::hasParamWithValue(const char* paramKey) const {
1348 return m_paramsWithValue.find(std::string(paramKey)) != m_paramsWithValue.end();
1349}
1350
1351const char* CommandLineArgs::getParamValue(const char* paramKey) const {
1352 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>::const_iterator iter = m_paramsWithValue.find(std::string(paramKey));
1353 return iter != m_paramsWithValue.end() ? iter->second.c_str() : "";
1354}
1355
1356bool CommandLineArgs::hasParam(const char* paramKey) const {
1357 return std::find(m_params.begin(), m_params.end(), std::string(paramKey)) != m_params.end();
1358}
1359
1360bool CommandLineArgs::empty(void) const {
1361 return m_params.empty() && m_paramsWithValue.empty();
1362}
1363
1364std::size_t CommandLineArgs::size(void) const {
1365 return m_params.size() + m_paramsWithValue.size();
1366}
1367
1368base::type::ostream_t& operator<<(base::type::ostream_t& os, const CommandLineArgs& c) {
1369 for (int i = 1; i < c.m_argc; ++i) {
1370 os << ELPP_LITERAL("[") << c.m_argv[i] << ELPP_LITERAL("]");
1371 if (i < c.m_argc - 1) {
1372 os << ELPP_LITERAL(" ");
1373 }
1374 }
1375 return os;
1376}

1406 width = base::consts::kDefaultSubsecondPrecision;

1415 break;
1416 case 5:
1417 m_offset = 10;
1418 break;
1419 case 6:

1421 break;
1422 default:
1423 m_offset = 1000;
1424 break;
1425 }

1483/// @brief Updates format to be used while logging.
1484/// @param userFormat User provided format
1485void LogFormat::parseFromFormat(const base::type::string_t& userFormat) {
1486 // We make copy because we will be changing the format
1487 // i.e, removing user provided date format from original format
1488 // and then storing it.
1489 base::type::string_t formatCopy = userFormat;
1490 m_flags = 0x0;
1491 auto conditionalAddFlag = [&](const base::type::char_t* specifier, base::FormatFlags flag) {
1492 std::size_t foundAt = base::type::string_t::npos;
1493 while ((foundAt = formatCopy.find(specifier, foundAt + 1)) != base::type::string_t::npos) {
1494 if (foundAt > 0 && formatCopy[foundAt - 1] == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar) {
1495 if (hasFlag(flag)) {
1496 // If we already have flag we remove the escape chars so that '%%' is turned to '%'
1497 // even after specifier resolution - this is because we only replaceFirst specifier
1498 formatCopy.erase(foundAt - 1, 1);
1499 ++foundAt;
1500 }
1501 } else {
1502 if (!hasFlag(flag)) addFlag(flag);
1503 }
1504 }
1505 };
1506 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kAppNameFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::AppName);
1507 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::Level);
1508 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::LevelShort);
1509 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLoggerIdFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::LoggerId);
1510 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kThreadIdFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::ThreadId);
1511 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLogFileFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::File);
1512 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLogFileBaseFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::FileBase);
1513 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLogLineFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::Line);
1514 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLogLocationFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::Location);
1515 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kLogFunctionFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::Function);
1516 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kCurrentUserFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::User);
1517 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kCurrentHostFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::Host);
1518 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kMessageFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::LogMessage);
1519 conditionalAddFlag(base::consts::kVerboseLevelFormatSpecifier, base::FormatFlags::VerboseLevel);
1520 // For date/time we need to extract user's date format first
1521 std::size_t dateIndex = std::string::npos;
1522 if ((dateIndex = formatCopy.find(base::consts::kDateTimeFormatSpecifier)) != std::string::npos) {
1523 while (dateIndex != std::string::npos && dateIndex > 0 && formatCopy[dateIndex - 1] == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar) {
1524 dateIndex = formatCopy.find(base::consts::kDateTimeFormatSpecifier, dateIndex + 1);
1525 }
1526 if (dateIndex != std::string::npos) {
1527 addFlag(base::FormatFlags::DateTime);
1528 updateDateFormat(dateIndex, formatCopy);
1529 }
1530 }
1531 m_format = formatCopy;
1532 updateFormatSpec();
1533}
1534
1535void LogFormat::updateDateFormat(std::size_t index, base::type::string_t& currFormat) {
1536 if (hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::DateTime)) {
1537 index += ELPP_STRLEN(base::consts::kDateTimeFormatSpecifier);
1538 }
1539 const base::type::char_t* ptr = currFormat.c_str() + index;
1540 if ((currFormat.size() > index) && (ptr[0] == '{')) {
1541 // User has provided format for date/time
1542 ++ptr;
1543 int count = 1; // Start by 1 in order to remove starting brace
1544 std::stringstream ss;
1545 for (; *ptr; ++ptr, ++count) {
1546 if (*ptr == '}') {
1547 ++count; // In order to remove ending brace
1548 break;
1549 }
1550 ss << static_cast<char>(*ptr);
1551 }
1552 currFormat.erase(index, count);
1553 m_dateTimeFormat = ss.str();
1554 } else {
1555 // No format provided, use default
1556 if (hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::DateTime)) {
1557 m_dateTimeFormat = std::string(base::consts::kDefaultDateTimeFormat);
1558 }
1559 }
1560}
1561
1562void LogFormat::updateFormatSpec(void) {
1563 // Do not use switch over strongly typed enums because Intel C++ compilers dont support them yet.
1564 if (m_level == Level::Debug) {
1565 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1566 base::consts::kDebugLevelLogValue);
1567 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1568 base::consts::kDebugLevelShortLogValue);
1569 } else if (m_level == Level::Info) {
1570 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1571 base::consts::kInfoLevelLogValue);
1572 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1573 base::consts::kInfoLevelShortLogValue);
1574 } else if (m_level == Level::Warning) {
1575 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1576 base::consts::kWarningLevelLogValue);
1577 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1578 base::consts::kWarningLevelShortLogValue);
1579 } else if (m_level == Level::Error) {
1580 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1581 base::consts::kErrorLevelLogValue);
1582 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1583 base::consts::kErrorLevelShortLogValue);
1584 } else if (m_level == Level::Fatal) {
1585 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1586 base::consts::kFatalLevelLogValue);
1587 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1588 base::consts::kFatalLevelShortLogValue);
1589 } else if (m_level == Level::Verbose) {
1590 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1591 base::consts::kVerboseLevelLogValue);
1592 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1593 base::consts::kVerboseLevelShortLogValue);
1594 } else if (m_level == Level::Trace) {
1595 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelFormatSpecifier,
1596 base::consts::kTraceLevelLogValue);
1597 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kSeverityLevelShortFormatSpecifier,
1598 base::consts::kTraceLevelShortLogValue);
1599 }
1600 if (hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::User)) {
1601 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kCurrentUserFormatSpecifier,
1602 m_currentUser);
1603 }
1604 if (hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::Host)) {
1605 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(m_format, base::consts::kCurrentHostFormatSpecifier,
1606 m_currentHost);
1607 }
1608 // Ignore Level::Global and Level::Unknown
1609}

1669
1670void TypedConfigurations::build(Configurations* configurations) {
1671 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
1672 auto getBool = [] (std::string boolStr) -> bool { // Pass by value for trimming
1673 base::utils::Str::trim(boolStr);
1674 return (boolStr == "TRUE" || boolStr == "true" || boolStr == "1");
1675 };
1676 std::vector<Configuration*> withFileSizeLimit;
1677 for (Configurations::const_iterator it = configurations->begin(); it != configurations->end(); ++it) {
1678 Configuration* conf = *it;
1679 // We cannot use switch on strong enums because Intel C++ dont support them yet
1680 if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::Enabled) {
1681 setValue(conf->level(), getBool(conf->value()), &m_enabledMap);
1682 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::ToFile) {
1683 setValue(conf->level(), getBool(conf->value()), &m_toFileMap);
1684 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::ToStandardOutput) {
1685 setValue(conf->level(), getBool(conf->value()), &m_toStandardOutputMap);
1686 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::Filename) {
1687 // We do not yet configure filename but we will configure in another
1688 // loop. This is because if file cannot be created, we will force ToFile
1689 // to be false. Because configuring logger is not necessarily performance
1690 // sensitive operation, we can live with another loop; (by the way this loop
1691 // is not very heavy either)
1692 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::Format) {
1693 setValue(conf->level(), base::LogFormat(conf->level(),
1694 base::type::string_t(conf->value().begin(), conf->value().end())), &m_logFormatMap);
1695 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::SubsecondPrecision) {
1696 setValue(Level::Global,
1697 base::SubsecondPrecision(static_cast<int>(getULong(conf->value()))), &m_subsecondPrecisionMap);
1698 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::PerformanceTracking) {
1699 setValue(Level::Global, getBool(conf->value()), &m_performanceTrackingMap);
1700 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::MaxLogFileSize) {
1701 auto v = getULong(conf->value());
1702 setValue(conf->level(), static_cast<std::size_t>(v), &m_maxLogFileSizeMap);
1703 if (v != 0) {
1704 withFileSizeLimit.push_back(conf);
1705 }
1706 } else if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::LogFlushThreshold) {
1707 setValue(conf->level(), static_cast<std::size_t>(getULong(conf->value())), &m_logFlushThresholdMap);
1708 }
1709 }
1710 // As mentioned earlier, we will now set filename configuration in separate loop to deal with non-existent files
1711 for (Configurations::const_iterator it = configurations->begin(); it != configurations->end(); ++it) {
1712 Configuration* conf = *it;
1713 if (conf->configurationType() == ConfigurationType::Filename) {
1714 insertFile(conf->level(), conf->value());
1715 }
1716 }
1717 for (std::vector<Configuration*>::iterator conf = withFileSizeLimit.begin();
1718 conf != withFileSizeLimit.end(); ++conf) {
1719 // This is not unsafe as mutex is locked in currect scope
1720 unsafeValidateFileRolling((*conf)->level(), base::defaultPreRollOutCallback);
1721 }
1722}
1723
1724unsigned long TypedConfigurations::getULong(std::string confVal) {
1725 bool valid = true;
1726 base::utils::Str::trim(confVal);
1727 valid = !confVal.empty() && std::find_if(confVal.begin(), confVal.end(),
1728 [](char c) {
1729 return !base::utils::Str::isDigit(c);
1730 }) == confVal.end();
1731 if (!valid) {
1732 valid = false;
1733 ELPP_ASSERT(valid, "Configuration value not a valid integer [" << confVal << "]");
1734 return 0;
1735 }
1736 return atol(confVal.c_str());
1737}
1738
1739std::string TypedConfigurations::resolveFilename(const std::string& filename) {
1740 std::string resultingFilename = filename;
1741 std::size_t dateIndex = std::string::npos;
1742 std::string dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr = std::string(base::consts::kDateTimeFormatSpecifierForFilename);
1743 if ((dateIndex = resultingFilename.find(dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr.c_str())) != std::string::npos) {
1744 while (dateIndex > 0 && resultingFilename[dateIndex - 1] == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar) {
1745 dateIndex = resultingFilename.find(dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr.c_str(), dateIndex + 1);
1746 }
1747 if (dateIndex != std::string::npos) {
1748 const char* ptr = resultingFilename.c_str() + dateIndex;
1749 // Goto end of specifier
1750 ptr += dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr.size();
1751 std::string fmt;
1752 if ((resultingFilename.size() > dateIndex) && (ptr[0] == '{')) {
1753 // User has provided format for date/time
1754 ++ptr;
1755 int count = 1; // Start by 1 in order to remove starting brace
1756 std::stringstream ss;
1757 for (; *ptr; ++ptr, ++count) {
1758 if (*ptr == '}') {
1759 ++count; // In order to remove ending brace
1760 break;
1761 }
1762 ss << *ptr;
1763 }
1764 resultingFilename.erase(dateIndex + dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr.size(), count);
1765 fmt = ss.str();
1766 } else {
1767 fmt = std::string(base::consts::kDefaultDateTimeFormatInFilename);
1768 }
1769 base::SubsecondPrecision ssPrec(3);
1770 std::string now = base::utils::DateTime::getDateTime(fmt.c_str(), &ssPrec);
1771 base::utils::Str::replaceAll(now, '/', '-'); // Replace path element since we are dealing with filename
1772 base::utils::Str::replaceAll(resultingFilename, dateTimeFormatSpecifierStr, now);
1773 }
1774 }
1775 return resultingFilename;
1776}
1777
1778void TypedConfigurations::insertFile(Level level, const std::string& fullFilename) {
1779 std::string resolvedFilename = resolveFilename(fullFilename);
1780 if (resolvedFilename.empty()) {
1781 std::cerr << "Could not load empty file for logging, please re-check your configurations for level ["
1782 << LevelHelper::convertToString(level) << "]";
1783 }
1784 std::string filePath = base::utils::File::extractPathFromFilename(resolvedFilename, base::consts::kFilePathSeparator);
1785 if (filePath.size() < resolvedFilename.size()) {
1786 base::utils::File::createPath(filePath);
1787 }
1788 auto create = [&](Level level) {
1789 base::LogStreamsReferenceMap::iterator filestreamIter = m_logStreamsReference->find(resolvedFilename);
1790 base::type::fstream_t* fs = nullptr;
1791 if (filestreamIter == m_logStreamsReference->end()) {
1792 // We need a completely new stream, nothing to share with
1793 fs = base::utils::File::newFileStream(resolvedFilename);
1794 m_filenameMap.insert(std::make_pair(level, resolvedFilename));
1795 m_fileStreamMap.insert(std::make_pair(level, base::FileStreamPtr(fs)));
1796 m_logStreamsReference->insert(std::make_pair(resolvedFilename, base::FileStreamPtr(m_fileStreamMap.at(level))));
1797 } else {
1798 // Woops! we have an existing one, share it!
1799 m_filenameMap.insert(std::make_pair(level, filestreamIter->first));
1800 m_fileStreamMap.insert(std::make_pair(level, base::FileStreamPtr(filestreamIter->second)));
1801 fs = filestreamIter->second.get();
1802 }
1803 if (fs == nullptr) {
1804 // We display bad file error from newFileStream()
1805 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Setting [TO_FILE] of ["
1806 << LevelHelper::convertToString(level) << "] to FALSE", false);
1807 setValue(level, false, &m_toFileMap);
1808 }
1809 };
1810 // If we dont have file conf for any level, create it for Level::Global first
1811 // otherwise create for specified level
1812 create(m_filenameMap.empty() && m_fileStreamMap.empty() ? Level::Global : level);
1813}
1814
1815bool TypedConfigurations::unsafeValidateFileRolling(Level level, const PreRollOutCallback& preRollOutCallback) {
1816 base::type::fstream_t* fs = unsafeGetConfigByRef(level, &m_fileStreamMap, "fileStream").get();
1817 if (fs == nullptr) {
1818 return true;
1819 }
1820 std::size_t maxLogFileSize = unsafeGetConfigByVal(level, &m_maxLogFileSizeMap, "maxLogFileSize");
1821 std::size_t currFileSize = base::utils::File::getSizeOfFile(fs);
1822 if (maxLogFileSize != 0 && currFileSize >= maxLogFileSize) {
1823 std::string fname = unsafeGetConfigByRef(level, &m_filenameMap, "filename");
1824 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Truncating log file [" << fname << "] as a result of configurations for level ["
1825 << LevelHelper::convertToString(level) << "]");
1826 fs->close();
1827 preRollOutCallback(fname.c_str(), currFileSize);
1828 fs->open(fname, std::fstream::out | std::fstream::trunc);
1829 return true;
1830 }
1831 return false;
1832}

1834// RegisteredHitCounters
1835
1836bool RegisteredHitCounters::validateEveryN(const char* filename, base::type::LineNumber lineNumber, std::size_t n) {
1837 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
1838 base::HitCounter* counter = get(filename, lineNumber);
1839 if (counter == nullptr) {
1840 registerNew(counter = new base::HitCounter(filename, lineNumber));
1841 }
1842 counter->validateHitCounts(n);
1843 bool result = (n >= 1 && counter->hitCounts() != 0 && counter->hitCounts() % n == 0);
1844 return result;
1845}
1846
1847/// @brief Validates counter for hits >= N, i.e, registers new if does not exist otherwise updates original one
1848/// @return True if validation resulted in triggering hit. Meaning logs should be written everytime true is returned
1849bool RegisteredHitCounters::validateAfterN(const char* filename, base::type::LineNumber lineNumber, std::size_t n) {
1850 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
1851 base::HitCounter* counter = get(filename, lineNumber);
1852 if (counter == nullptr) {
1853 registerNew(counter = new base::HitCounter(filename, lineNumber));
1854 }
1855 // Do not use validateHitCounts here since we do not want to reset counter here
1856 // Note the >= instead of > because we are incrementing
1857 // after this check
1858 if (counter->hitCounts() >= n)
1859 return true;
1860 counter->increment();
1861 return false;
1862}
1863
1864/// @brief Validates counter for hits are <= n, i.e, registers new if does not exist otherwise updates original one
1865/// @return True if validation resulted in triggering hit. Meaning logs should be written everytime true is returned
1866bool RegisteredHitCounters::validateNTimes(const char* filename, base::type::LineNumber lineNumber, std::size_t n) {
1867 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
1868 base::HitCounter* counter = get(filename, lineNumber);
1869 if (counter == nullptr) {
1870 registerNew(counter = new base::HitCounter(filename, lineNumber));
1871 }
1872 counter->increment();
1873 // Do not use validateHitCounts here since we do not want to reset counter here
1874 if (counter->hitCounts() <= n)
1875 return true;
1876 return false;
1877}

1901 : m_loggerRegistrationCallbacks) {

1946
1947void VRegistry::setModules(const char* modules) {
1948 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
1949 auto addSuffix = [](std::stringstream& ss, const char* sfx, const char* prev) {
1950 if (prev != nullptr && base::utils::Str::endsWith(ss.str(), std::string(prev))) {
1951 std::string chr(ss.str().substr(0, ss.str().size() - strlen(prev)));
1952 ss.str(std::string(""));
1953 ss << chr;
1954 }
1955 if (base::utils::Str::endsWith(ss.str(), std::string(sfx))) {
1956 std::string chr(ss.str().substr(0, ss.str().size() - strlen(sfx)));
1957 ss.str(std::string(""));
1958 ss << chr;
1959 }
1960 ss << sfx;
1961 };
1962 auto insert = [&](std::stringstream& ss, base::type::VerboseLevel level) {
1963 if (!base::utils::hasFlag(LoggingFlag::DisableVModulesExtensions, *m_pFlags)) {
1964 addSuffix(ss, ".h", nullptr);
1965 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1966 addSuffix(ss, ".c", ".h");
1967 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1968 addSuffix(ss, ".cpp", ".c");
1969 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1970 addSuffix(ss, ".cc", ".cpp");
1971 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1972 addSuffix(ss, ".cxx", ".cc");
1973 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1974 addSuffix(ss, ".-inl.h", ".cxx");
1975 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1976 addSuffix(ss, ".hxx", ".-inl.h");
1977 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1978 addSuffix(ss, ".hpp", ".hxx");
1979 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1980 addSuffix(ss, ".hh", ".hpp");
1981 }
1982 m_modules.insert(std::make_pair(ss.str(), level));
1983 };
1984 bool isMod = true;
1985 bool isLevel = false;
1986 std::stringstream ss;
1987 int level = -1;
1988 for (; *modules; ++modules) {
1989 switch (*modules) {
1990 case '=':
1991 isLevel = true;
1992 isMod = false;
1993 break;
1994 case ',':
1995 isLevel = false;
1996 isMod = true;
1997 if (!ss.str().empty() && level != -1) {
1998 insert(ss, static_cast<base::type::VerboseLevel>(level));
1999 ss.str(std::string(""));
2000 level = -1;
2001 }
2002 break;
2003 default:
2004 if (isMod) {
2005 ss << *modules;
2006 } else if (isLevel) {
2007 if (isdigit(*modules)) {
2008 level = static_cast<base::type::VerboseLevel>(*modules) - 48;
2009 }
2010 }
2011 break;
2012 }
2013 }
2014 if (!ss.str().empty() && level != -1) {
2015 insert(ss, static_cast<base::type::VerboseLevel>(level));
2016 }
2017}
2018
2019bool VRegistry::allowed(base::type::VerboseLevel vlevel, const char* file) {
2020 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(lock());
2021 if (m_modules.empty() || file == nullptr) {
2022 return vlevel <= m_level;
2023 } else {
2024 char baseFilename[base::consts::kSourceFilenameMaxLength] = "";
2025 base::utils::File::buildBaseFilename(file, baseFilename);
2026 std::unordered_map<std::string, base::type::VerboseLevel>::iterator it = m_modules.begin();
2027 for (; it != m_modules.end(); ++it) {
2028 if (base::utils::Str::wildCardMatch(baseFilename, it->first.c_str())) {
2029 return vlevel <= it->second;
2030 }
2031 }
2032 if (base::utils::hasFlag(LoggingFlag::AllowVerboseIfModuleNotSpecified, *m_pFlags)) {
2033 return true;
2034 }
2035 return false;
2036 }
2037}

2209#endif

2214
2215void DefaultLogDispatchCallback::dispatch(base::type::string_t&& logLine) {
2216 if (m_data->dispatchAction() == base::DispatchAction::NormalLog) {
2217 if (m_data->logMessage()->logger()->m_typedConfigurations->toFile(m_data->logMessage()->level())) {
2218 base::type::fstream_t* fs = m_data->logMessage()->logger()->m_typedConfigurations->fileStream(
2219 m_data->logMessage()->level());
2220 if (fs != nullptr) {
2221 fs->write(logLine.c_str(), logLine.size());
2222 if (fs->fail()) {
2223 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Unable to write log to file ["
2224 << m_data->logMessage()->logger()->m_typedConfigurations->filename(m_data->logMessage()->level()) << "].\n"
2225 << "Few possible reasons (could be something else):\n" << " * Permission denied\n"
2226 << " * Disk full\n" << " * Disk is not writable", true);
2227 } else {
2228 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::ImmediateFlush)
2229 || (m_data->logMessage()->logger()->isFlushNeeded(m_data->logMessage()->level()))) {
2230 m_data->logMessage()->logger()->flush(m_data->logMessage()->level(), fs);
2231 }
2232 }
2233 } else {
2234 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Log file for [" << LevelHelper::convertToString(m_data->logMessage()->level()) << "] "
2235 << "has not been configured but [TO_FILE] is configured to TRUE. [Logger ID: "
2236 << m_data->logMessage()->logger()->id() << "]", false);
2237 }
2238 }
2239 if (m_data->logMessage()->logger()->m_typedConfigurations->toStandardOutput(m_data->logMessage()->level())) {
2240 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::ColoredTerminalOutput))
2241 m_data->logMessage()->logger()->logBuilder()->convertToColoredOutput(&logLine, m_data->logMessage()->level());
2242 ELPP_COUT << ELPP_COUT_LINE(logLine);
2243 }
2244 }
2245#if defined(ELPP_SYSLOG)
2246 else if (m_data->dispatchAction() == base::DispatchAction::SysLog) {
2247 // Determine syslog priority
2248 int sysLogPriority = 0;
2249 if (m_data->logMessage()->level() == Level::Fatal)
2250 sysLogPriority = LOG_EMERG;
2251 else if (m_data->logMessage()->level() == Level::Error)
2252 sysLogPriority = LOG_ERR;
2253 else if (m_data->logMessage()->level() == Level::Warning)
2254 sysLogPriority = LOG_WARNING;
2255 else if (m_data->logMessage()->level() == Level::Info)
2256 sysLogPriority = LOG_INFO;
2257 else if (m_data->logMessage()->level() == Level::Debug)
2258 sysLogPriority = LOG_DEBUG;
2259 else
2260 sysLogPriority = LOG_NOTICE;
2261# if defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
2262 char* line = base::utils::Str::wcharPtrToCharPtr(logLine.c_str());
2263 syslog(sysLogPriority, "%s", line);
2264 free(line);
2265# else
2266 syslog(sysLogPriority, "%s", logLine.c_str());
2267# endif
2268 }
2269#endif // defined(ELPP_SYSLOG)
2270}

2303bool AsyncDispatchWorker::clean(void) {
2304 std::mutex m;
2305 std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lk(m);
2306 cv.wait(lk, [] { return !ELPP->asyncLogQueue()->empty(); });
2307 emptyQueue();
2308 lk.unlock();
2309 cv.notify_one();
2310 return ELPP->asyncLogQueue()->empty();
2311}

2313void AsyncDispatchWorker::emptyQueue(void) {
2314 while (!ELPP->asyncLogQueue()->empty()) {
2315 AsyncLogItem data = ELPP->asyncLogQueue()->next();
2316 handle(&data);
2317 base::threading::msleep(100);
2318 }
2319}

2325 t1.join();

2327
2328void AsyncDispatchWorker::handle(AsyncLogItem* logItem) {
2329 LogDispatchData* data = logItem->data();
2330 LogMessage* logMessage = logItem->logMessage();
2331 Logger* logger = logMessage->logger();
2332 base::TypedConfigurations* conf = logger->typedConfigurations();
2333 base::type::string_t logLine = logItem->logLine();
2334 if (data->dispatchAction() == base::DispatchAction::NormalLog) {
2335 if (conf->toFile(logMessage->level())) {
2336 base::type::fstream_t* fs = conf->fileStream(logMessage->level());
2337 if (fs != nullptr) {
2338 fs->write(logLine.c_str(), logLine.size());
2339 if (fs->fail()) {
2340 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Unable to write log to file ["
2341 << conf->filename(logMessage->level()) << "].\n"
2342 << "Few possible reasons (could be something else):\n" << " * Permission denied\n"
2343 << " * Disk full\n" << " * Disk is not writable", true);
2344 } else {
2345 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::ImmediateFlush) || (logger->isFlushNeeded(logMessage->level()))) {
2346 logger->flush(logMessage->level(), fs);
2347 }
2348 }
2349 } else {
2350 ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Log file for [" << LevelHelper::convertToString(logMessage->level()) << "] "
2351 << "has not been configured but [TO_FILE] is configured to TRUE. [Logger ID: " << logger->id() << "]", false);
2352 }
2353 }
2354 }
2355# if defined(ELPP_SYSLOG)
2356 else if (data->dispatchAction() == base::DispatchAction::SysLog) {
2357 // Determine syslog priority
2358 int sysLogPriority = 0;
2359 if (logMessage->level() == Level::Fatal)
2360 sysLogPriority = LOG_EMERG;
2361 else if (logMessage->level() == Level::Error)
2362 sysLogPriority = LOG_ERR;
2363 else if (logMessage->level() == Level::Warning)
2364 sysLogPriority = LOG_WARNING;
2365 else if (logMessage->level() == Level::Info)
2366 sysLogPriority = LOG_INFO;
2367 else if (logMessage->level() == Level::Debug)
2368 sysLogPriority = LOG_DEBUG;
2369 else
2370 sysLogPriority = LOG_NOTICE;
2371# if defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
2372 char* line = base::utils::Str::wcharPtrToCharPtr(logLine.c_str());
2373 syslog(sysLogPriority, "%s", line);
2374 free(line);
2375# else
2376 syslog(sysLogPriority, "%s", logLine.c_str());
2377# endif
2378 }
2379# endif // defined(ELPP_SYSLOG)
2380}

2386 }

2390// DefaultLogBuilder
2391
2392base::type::string_t DefaultLogBuilder::build(const LogMessage* logMessage, bool appendNewLine) const {
2393 base::TypedConfigurations* tc = logMessage->logger()->typedConfigurations();
2394 const base::LogFormat* logFormat = &tc->logFormat(logMessage->level());
2395 base::type::string_t logLine = logFormat->format();
2396 char buff[base::consts::kSourceFilenameMaxLength + base::consts::kSourceLineMaxLength] = "";
2397 const char* bufLim = buff + sizeof(buff);
2398 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::AppName)) {
2399 // App name
2400 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kAppNameFormatSpecifier,
2401 logMessage->logger()->parentApplicationName());
2402 }
2403 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::ThreadId)) {
2404 // Thread ID
2405 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kThreadIdFormatSpecifier,
2406 ELPP->getThreadName(base::threading::getCurrentThreadId()));
2407 }
2408 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::DateTime)) {
2409 // DateTime
2410 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kDateTimeFormatSpecifier,
2411 base::utils::DateTime::getDateTime(logFormat->dateTimeFormat().c_str(),
2412 &tc->subsecondPrecision(logMessage->level())));
2413 }
2414 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::Function)) {
2415 // Function
2416 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kLogFunctionFormatSpecifier, logMessage->func());
2417 }
2418 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::File)) {
2419 // File
2420 base::utils::Str::clearBuff(buff, base::consts::kSourceFilenameMaxLength);
2421 base::utils::File::buildStrippedFilename(logMessage->file().c_str(), buff);
2422 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kLogFileFormatSpecifier, std::string(buff));
2423 }
2424 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::FileBase)) {
2425 // FileBase
2426 base::utils::Str::clearBuff(buff, base::consts::kSourceFilenameMaxLength);
2427 base::utils::File::buildBaseFilename(logMessage->file(), buff);
2428 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kLogFileBaseFormatSpecifier, std::string(buff));
2429 }
2430 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::Line)) {
2431 // Line
2432 char* buf = base::utils::Str::clearBuff(buff, base::consts::kSourceLineMaxLength);
2433 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(logMessage->line(), base::consts::kSourceLineMaxLength, buf, bufLim, false);
2434 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kLogLineFormatSpecifier, std::string(buff));
2435 }
2436 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::Location)) {
2437 // Location
2438 char* buf = base::utils::Str::clearBuff(buff,
2439 base::consts::kSourceFilenameMaxLength + base::consts::kSourceLineMaxLength);
2440 base::utils::File::buildStrippedFilename(logMessage->file().c_str(), buff);
2441 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(buff, buf, bufLim);
2442 buf = base::utils::Str::addToBuff(":", buf, bufLim);
2443 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(logMessage->line(), base::consts::kSourceLineMaxLength, buf, bufLim,
2444 false);
2445 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kLogLocationFormatSpecifier, std::string(buff));
2446 }
2447 if (logMessage->level() == Level::Verbose && logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::VerboseLevel)) {
2448 // Verbose level
2449 char* buf = base::utils::Str::clearBuff(buff, 1);
2450 buf = base::utils::Str::convertAndAddToBuff(logMessage->verboseLevel(), 1, buf, bufLim, false);
2451 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kVerboseLevelFormatSpecifier, std::string(buff));
2452 }
2453 if (logFormat->hasFlag(base::FormatFlags::LogMessage)) {
2454 // Log message
2455 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, base::consts::kMessageFormatSpecifier, logMessage->message());
2456 }
2457#if !defined(ELPP_DISABLE_CUSTOM_FORMAT_SPECIFIERS)
2458 el::base::threading::ScopedLock lock_(ELPP->customFormatSpecifiersLock());
2459 ELPP_UNUSED(lock_);
2460 for (std::vector<CustomFormatSpecifier>::const_iterator it = ELPP->customFormatSpecifiers()->begin();
2461 it != ELPP->customFormatSpecifiers()->end(); ++it) {
2462 std::string fs(it->formatSpecifier());
2463 base::type::string_t wcsFormatSpecifier(fs.begin(), fs.end());
2464 base::utils::Str::replaceFirstWithEscape(logLine, wcsFormatSpecifier, it->resolver()(logMessage));
2465 }
2466#endif // !defined(ELPP_DISABLE_CUSTOM_FORMAT_SPECIFIERS)
2467 if (appendNewLine) logLine += ELPP_LITERAL("\n");
2468 return logLine;
2469}

2471// LogDispatcher
2472
2473void LogDispatcher::dispatch(void) {
2474 if (m_proceed && m_dispatchAction == base::DispatchAction::None) {
2475 m_proceed = false;
2476 }
2477 if (!m_proceed) {
2478 return;
2479 }
2480#ifndef ELPP_NO_GLOBAL_LOCK
2481 // see https://github.com/muflihun/easyloggingpp/issues/580
2482 // global lock is turned on by default unless
2483 // ELPP_NO_GLOBAL_LOCK is defined
2484 base::threading::ScopedLock scopedLock(ELPP->lock());
2485#endif
2486 base::TypedConfigurations* tc = m_logMessage->logger()->m_typedConfigurations;
2487 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::StrictLogFileSizeCheck)) {
2488 tc->validateFileRolling(m_logMessage->level(), ELPP->preRollOutCallback());
2489 }
2490 LogDispatchCallback* callback = nullptr;
2491 LogDispatchData data;
2492 for (const std::pair<std::string, base::type::LogDispatchCallbackPtr>& h
2493 : ELPP->m_logDispatchCallbacks) {
2494 callback = h.second.get();
2495 if (callback != nullptr && callback->enabled()) {
2496 data.setLogMessage(m_logMessage);
2497 data.setDispatchAction(m_dispatchAction);
2498 callback->handle(&data);
2499 }
2500 }
2501}

2537
2538Writer& Writer::construct(int count, const char* loggerIds, ...) {
2539 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::MultiLoggerSupport)) {
2540 va_list loggersList;
2541 va_start(loggersList, loggerIds);
2542 const char* id = loggerIds;
2543 m_loggerIds.reserve(count);
2544 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
2545 m_loggerIds.push_back(std::string(id));
2546 id = va_arg(loggersList, const char*);
2547 }
2548 va_end(loggersList);
2549 initializeLogger(m_loggerIds.at(0));
2550 } else {
2551 initializeLogger(std::string(loggerIds));
2552 }
2553 m_messageBuilder.initialize(m_logger);
2554 return *this;
2555}
2556
2557void Writer::initializeLogger(const std::string& loggerId, bool lookup, bool needLock) {
2558 if (lookup) {
2559 m_logger = ELPP->registeredLoggers()->get(loggerId, ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::CreateLoggerAutomatically));
2560 }
2561 if (m_logger == nullptr) {
2562 {
2563 if (!ELPP->registeredLoggers()->has(std::string(base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId))) {
2564 // Somehow default logger has been unregistered. Not good! Register again
2565 ELPP->registeredLoggers()->get(std::string(base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId));
2566 }
2567 }
2568 Writer(Level::Debug, m_file, m_line, m_func).construct(1, base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId)
2569 << "Logger [" << loggerId << "] is not registered yet!";
2570 m_proceed = false;
2571 } else {
2572 if (needLock) {
2573 m_logger->acquireLock(); // This should not be unlocked by checking m_proceed because
2574 // m_proceed can be changed by lines below
2575 }
2576 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::HierarchicalLogging)) {
2577 m_proceed = m_level == Level::Verbose ? m_logger->enabled(m_level) :
2578 LevelHelper::castToInt(m_level) >= LevelHelper::castToInt(ELPP->m_loggingLevel);
2579 } else {
2580 m_proceed = m_logger->enabled(m_level);
2581 }
2582 }
2583}
2584
2585void Writer::processDispatch() {
2586#if ELPP_LOGGING_ENABLED
2587 if (ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::MultiLoggerSupport)) {
2588 bool firstDispatched = false;
2589 base::type::string_t logMessage;
2590 std::size_t i = 0;
2591 do {
2592 if (m_proceed) {
2593 if (firstDispatched) {
2594 m_logger->stream() << logMessage;
2595 } else {
2596 firstDispatched = true;
2597 if (m_loggerIds.size() > 1) {
2598 logMessage = m_logger->stream().str();
2599 }
2600 }
2601 triggerDispatch();
2602 } else if (m_logger != nullptr) {
2603 m_logger->stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
2604 m_logger->releaseLock();
2605 }
2606 if (i + 1 < m_loggerIds.size()) {
2607 initializeLogger(m_loggerIds.at(i + 1));
2608 }
2609 } while (++i < m_loggerIds.size());
2610 } else {
2611 if (m_proceed) {
2612 triggerDispatch();
2613 } else if (m_logger != nullptr) {
2614 m_logger->stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
2615 m_logger->releaseLock();
2616 }
2617 }
2618#else
2619 if (m_logger != nullptr) {
2620 m_logger->stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
2621 m_logger->releaseLock();
2622 }
2623#endif // ELPP_LOGGING_ENABLED
2624}
2625
2626void Writer::triggerDispatch(void) {
2627 try {
2628 if (m_proceed) {
2629 if (m_msg == nullptr) {
2630 LogMessage msg(m_level, m_file, m_line, m_func, m_verboseLevel,
2631 m_logger);
2632 base::LogDispatcher(m_proceed, &msg, m_dispatchAction).dispatch();
2633 } else {
2634 base::LogDispatcher(m_proceed, m_msg, m_dispatchAction).dispatch();
2635 }
2636 }
2637 if (m_logger != nullptr) {
2638 m_logger->stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
2639 m_logger->releaseLock();
2640 }
2641 if (m_proceed && m_level == Level::Fatal
2642 && !ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::DisableApplicationAbortOnFatalLog)) {
2643 base::Writer(Level::Warning, m_file, m_line, m_func).construct(1, base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId)
2644 << "Aborting application. Reason: Fatal log at [" << m_file << ":" << m_line << "]";
2645 std::stringstream reasonStream;
2646 reasonStream << "Fatal log at [" << m_file << ":" << m_line << "]"
2647 << " If you wish to disable 'abort on fatal log' please use "
2648 << "el::Loggers::addFlag(el::LoggingFlag::DisableApplicationAbortOnFatalLog)";
2649 base::utils::abort(1, reasonStream.str());
2650 }
2651 m_proceed = false;
2652 }
2653 catch(std::exception & ex){
2654 // Extremely low memory situation; don't let exception be unhandled.
2655 }
2656}

2791
2792void StackTrace::generateNew(void) {
2793#ifdef HAVE_EXECINFO
2794 m_stack.clear();
2795 void* stack[kMaxStack];
2796 unsigned int size = backtrace(stack, kMaxStack);
2797 char** strings = backtrace_symbols(stack, size);
2798 if (size > kStackStart) { // Skip StackTrace c'tor and generateNew
2799 for (std::size_t i = kStackStart; i < size; ++i) {
2800 std::string mangName;
2801 std::string location;
2802 std::string hex;
2803 std::string addr;
2804
2805 // entry: 2 crash.cpp.bin 0x0000000101552be5 _ZN2el4base5debug10StackTraceC1Ev + 21
2806 const std::string line(strings[i]);
2807 auto p = line.find("_");
2808 if (p != std::string::npos) {
2809 mangName = line.substr(p);
2810 mangName = mangName.substr(0, mangName.find(" +"));
2811 }
2812 p = line.find("0x");
2813 if (p != std::string::npos) {
2814 addr = line.substr(p);
2815 addr = addr.substr(0, addr.find("_"));
2816 }
2817 // Perform demangling if parsed properly
2818 if (!mangName.empty()) {
2819 int status = 0;
2820 char* demangName = abi::__cxa_demangle(mangName.data(), 0, 0, &status);
2821 // if demangling is successful, output the demangled function name
2822 if (status == 0) {
2823 // Success (see http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/libstdc++-html-USERS-4.3/a01696.html)
2824 StackTraceEntry entry(i - 1, location, demangName, hex, addr);
2825 m_stack.push_back(entry);
2826 } else {
2827 // Not successful - we will use mangled name
2828 StackTraceEntry entry(i - 1, location, mangName, hex, addr);
2829 m_stack.push_back(entry);
2830 }
2831 free(demangName);
2832 } else {
2833 StackTraceEntry entry(i - 1, line);
2834 m_stack.push_back(entry);
2835 }
2836 }
2837 }
2838 free(strings);
2839#else
2840 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Stacktrace generation not supported for selected compiler");
2841#endif // ELPP_STACKTRACE
2842}

2844// Static helper functions
2845
2846static std::string crashReason(int sig) {
2847 std::stringstream ss;
2848 bool foundReason = false;
2849 for (int i = 0; i < base::consts::kCrashSignalsCount; ++i) {
2850 if (base::consts::kCrashSignals[i].numb == sig) {
2851 ss << "Application has crashed due to [" << base::consts::kCrashSignals[i].name << "] signal";
2852 if (ELPP->hasFlag(el::LoggingFlag::LogDetailedCrashReason)) {
2853 ss << std::endl <<
2854 " " << base::consts::kCrashSignals[i].brief << std::endl <<
2855 " " << base::consts::kCrashSignals[i].detail;
2856 }
2857 foundReason = true;
2858 }
2859 }
2860 if (!foundReason) {
2861 ss << "Application has crashed due to unknown signal [" << sig << "]";
2862 }
2863 return ss.str();
2864}
2865/// @brief Logs reason of crash from sig
2866static void logCrashReason(int sig, bool stackTraceIfAvailable, Level level, const char* logger) {
2867 if (sig == SIGINT && ELPP->hasFlag(el::LoggingFlag::IgnoreSigInt)) {
2868 return;
2869 }
2870 std::stringstream ss;
2871 ss << "CRASH HANDLED; ";
2872 ss << crashReason(sig);
2873#if ELPP_STACKTRACE
2874 if (stackTraceIfAvailable) {
2875 ss << std::endl << " ======= Backtrace: =========" << std::endl << base::debug::StackTrace();
2876 }
2877#else
2878 ELPP_UNUSED(stackTraceIfAvailable);
2879#endif // ELPP_STACKTRACE
2880 ELPP_WRITE_LOG(el::base::Writer, level, base::DispatchAction::NormalLog, logger) << ss.str();
2881}

2887/// @brief Default application crash handler
2888///
2889/// @detail This function writes log using 'default' logger, prints stack trace for GCC based compilers and aborts program.

2891 base::debug::logCrashReason(sig, true, Level::Fatal, base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId);
2892 base::debug::crashAbort(sig);

3031void Loggers::configureFromGlobal(const char* globalConfigurationFilePath) {
3032 std::ifstream gcfStream(globalConfigurationFilePath, std::ifstream::in);
3033 ELPP_ASSERT(gcfStream.is_open(), "Unable to open global configuration file [" << globalConfigurationFilePath
3034 << "] for parsing.");
3035 std::string line = std::string();
3036 std::stringstream ss;
3037 Logger* logger = nullptr;
3038 auto configure = [&](void) {
3039 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(8, "Configuring logger: '" << logger->id() << "' with configurations \n" << ss.str()
3040 << "\n--------------");
3041 Configurations c;
3042 c.parseFromText(ss.str());
3043 logger->configure(c);
3044 };
3045 while (gcfStream.good()) {
3046 std::getline(gcfStream, line);
3047 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Parsing line: " << line);
3048 base::utils::Str::trim(line);
3049 if (Configurations::Parser::isComment(line)) continue;
3050 Configurations::Parser::ignoreComments(&line);
3051 base::utils::Str::trim(line);
3052 if (line.size() > 2 && base::utils::Str::startsWith(line, std::string(base::consts::kConfigurationLoggerId))) {
3053 if (!ss.str().empty() && logger != nullptr) {
3054 configure();
3055 }
3056 ss.str(std::string(""));
3057 line = line.substr(2);
3058 base::utils::Str::trim(line);
3059 if (line.size() > 1) {
3060 ELPP_INTERNAL_INFO(1, "Getting logger: '" << line << "'");
3061 logger = getLogger(line);
3062 }
3063 } else {
3064 ss << line << "\n";
3065 }
3066 }
3067 if (!ss.str().empty() && logger != nullptr) {
3068 configure();
3069 }
3070}
